    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/publisher> <http://dataportal.se/organisation/SE2021004953>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "Photogrammetric 3D model of a helmet fitting fragment from Vendel Boat Grave 10 in Vendel, Uppsala. The fragment, which would have sat between the eyebrows, depicts a stylized serpent head and is dated to the eponymous Vendel Period. It is currently held in the collections of the National Historical Museums in Stockholm. \n\nLink to the Dynamic Collections platform  \n\nhttps://dyncoll.ht.lu.se/artifact_view.php?item=977\n\nLink to Sök I Samlingarna  \n\nhttps://samlingar.shm.se/object/ab807fe8-b254-4e30-9f45-ec4fec544a5c"@en;
