<https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/caeef827c14ca0358edb746237cb46a7> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/language> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/language/ENG>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/publisher> <http://dataportal.se/organisation/SE2021004060>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "Green Chromatic Index (GCI) also known as Green Chromatic Coordinate (GCC) is a measure of the greenness of vegetation.  It is calculated from daily averaged RGB (Red, Green, Blue) composites values of digital images captured by PhenoCams.\nAbisko Scientific Research Station (2022). Phenocam - Green Chromatic Coordinates (GCC) Composite Image Mean Values from Abisko Scientific Research Station, Mast 4.5m Phenocam 01, 2021-04-01��2021-11-30 [Data set]. Swedish Infrastructure for Ecosystem Science (SITES). https://hdl.handle.net/11676.1/0c1uPfpuoGdfr_TCiC04cfuU"@en;
